<subSubSection id="079E653C5378FFB6FEF38424FBC7FE7F" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75378FFB6FEF38424FBC7FE7F" blockId="38.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55378FFB6FEF38424FE9CFEEF" bold="true" box="[199,308,295,321]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345378FFB6FF728424FDE4FEEE" baseAuthorityName="Delle Chiaje" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[326,588,295,321]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55378FFB6FF728424FDE4FEEE" box="[326,588,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Amphipholis squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a polyphyletic (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465378FFB6FD198424FBB8FEEF" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Hugall, A. F. &amp; Thuy, B. &amp; Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V." box="[813,1040,295,321]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="415 - 430" refId="ref34885" refString="O'Hara, T. D., Hugall, A. F., Thuy, B., Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V. (2017) Restructuring higher taxonomy using broad-scale phylogenomics: the living Ophiuroidea. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 107, 415 - 430. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2016.12.006" type="journal article" year="2017">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55378FFB6FDBA8424FC62FEEF" box="[910,970,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
) assemblage of numerous genetic lineages (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465378FFB6FF368448FE73FECB" author="Boissin, E. &amp; Feral, J. P. &amp; Chenuil, A." box="[258,475,331,357]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1732 - 1744" refId="ref29362" refString="Boissin, E., Feral, J. P. &amp; Chenuil, A. (2008) Defining reproductively isolated units in a cryptic and syntopic species complex using mitochondrial and nuclear markers: the brooding brittle star, Amphipholis squamata (Ophiuroidea). Molecular Ecology, 17, 1732 - 1744. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 294 X. 2007.03652. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Boissin 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55378FFB6FF6B8448FE3FFECB" box="[351,407,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Only synonyms relevant to the SPA are listed above. The wide bathymetric range of the MD50 samples suggests that several lineages may be present in the SPA. 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465378FFB6FDD9846CFB20FE27" author="Hertz, M." box="[1005,1160,367,393]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref31692" refString="Hertz, M. (1927 a) Die Ophiuroiden der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar-Expedition, 19, 1 - 56, pls. 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1927">Hertz (1927a)</bibRefCitation>
named her specimens 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345378FFB6FBB0846CFF72FE02" baseAuthorityName="Doderlein" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55378FFB6FBB0846CFF72FE02" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">A. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after a South African lineage, however, the diagnostic characters used by 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465378FFB6FA3B8490FB78FE03" author="Doderlein, L." box="[1039,1232,403,429]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="245 - 258" refId="ref30668" refString="Doderlein, L. (1910) Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea, Echinoidea. In: Schultze, L. (Ed.), Forschungsreise im westlichen Sudafrica 4 (1). Denkschriften der Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 16, pp. 245 - 258, pls. 4 - 5." type="journal article" year="1910">Döderlein (1910)</bibRefCitation>
to distinguish this species were inadequate (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465378FFB6FF8084B4FDD5FE7F" author="Mortensen, T." box="[436,637,439,465]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="215 - 400" refId="ref34370" refString="Mortensen, T. (1933 a) Echinoderms of South Africa (Asteroidea: Ophiuroidea). Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening, 93, 215 - 400, pls. 8 - 19." type="journal article" year="1933">Mortensen 1933a</bibRefCitation>
). The MD50 material is small and damaged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
